  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nA very common testing scenario is to evaluate the effect of a transaction behind some other transaction (known as \"the offender\").\r\n\r\nThere is no easy way to do this in Forge right now, which makes it difficult to onboard from Hardhat where you can do something like:\r\n```\r\nexport async function forkIntraBlock(\r\n  txHash: string,\r\n  network: Network,\r\n  ethers: HardhatEthersHelpers,\r\n  archiveRpcUrl: string\r\n): Promise<void> {\r\n  const provider = new JsonRpcProvider(archiveRpcUrl)\r\n  const response = await provider.getTransaction(txHash)\r\n  const tx = getRawTransaction(response)\r\n  const receipt = await provider.getTransactionReceipt(txHash)\r\n\r\n  await network.provider.request({\r\n    method: 'hardhat_reset',\r\n    params: [\r\n      {\r\n        forking: {\r\n          jsonRpcUrl: archiveRpcUrl,\r\n          blockNumber: receipt.blockNumber - 1,\r\n        },\r\n      },\r\n    ],\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  await ethers.provider.sendTransaction(tx)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSome developers may wish to have the complete intra-block state, but generally it's enough to fork at a block and apply only the offender transaction.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
